## Key Findings

### The Three Crises

The research identifies a **convergence of three simultaneous crises** that GECKO sits at the intersection of:

1. **Execution Crisis** — AI coding tools are fast but not accurate; developers 19% slower on average with unstructured prompts
2. **Validation Crisis** — 90% of startups fail due to product-market mismatch; no structured pre-build validation tool exists
3. **Economics Crisis** — Subscription model is misaligned with developer usage patterns; strong demand for pay-per-use

### The Competitive Moat

No existing tool occupies GECKO's intersection:

| Layer | Owner | Gap |
|---|---|---|
| Code execution | Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot | Pre-build judgment |
| Spec writing | Kiro, Intent, BMAD | Adversarial market validation |
| Idea validation | Validator AI, generic LLMs | Structured output, repo-native artifacts |
| Payment rails | frames.ag, x402 Foundation | Intelligence layer governing *what* to spend on |
| Product planning | ChatPRD, Linear AI, Aha! | Single-prompt ICP + PRD + business plan |

### The One-Liner

> **Stop building things nobody wants. Paste your idea — get a build/kill verdict and a fundable PRD. Pay per run. No subscription.**

